# Mobile App Standards (Flutter/Dart)

## Core Responsibilities
The mobile app acts as a hardware-efficient sensor that wakes up ONLY when necessary during an active "Trip Session".

## Technical Constraints
- **Location Tracking:** NEVER use standard `setInterval` or continuous `Geolocator.getPositionStream` in the background. You MUST use native OS geofencing (e.g., `flutter_background_geolocation`).
- **Audio Processing:** TFLite (`sentinel_audio.tflite`) is strictly tied to an active trip. Implement a low-power hardware DSP decibel threshold listener to trigger the TFLite classification, avoiding continuous CPU usage.
- **State Management:** Use Riverpod or Bloc. Keep UI components perfectly isolated from platform channels.

## Coding Patterns
- Always handle `Permissions` gracefully. Provide rationale UI before requesting `Always Allow` location access.
- Implement an offline queue. If a `trip_ping` fails due to no network, cache it securely in SQLite/Hive and dispatch when connection is restored.